'''Infantophilia''' or '''nepiophilia''' (From Greek ''nepion'', "infant" + ''-philia'') is the primary sexual attraction of adults to very small children (defined by various studies as 0–4{{ref|studies}}).  This should not be confused with [[infantilism]] ("autonepiophilia").

